cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel framework for imbalance classification that aims to generate a strong ensemble by self-paced harmonizing data hardness via under-sampling. It also mentions that the existing learning methods suffer from poor performance or low computation efficiency under such a scenario, which is a common problem in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed framework involves generating a strong ensemble, which is a common technique in AI. 

The paper also mentions class overlapping, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS). 

Finally, the proposed framework involves boosting the performance of existing learning methods, which is a common problem in neural networks (cs.NE).
